FBIS4-63016 "drsov097_b_94039" FBIS-SOV-94-097 Daily Report 18 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Minimum Wages To Be Raised to 19,500 Rubles in Jun-Jul Minimum Wages To Be Raised to 19,500 Rubles in Jun-Jul MK1805124694 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 18 May 94 p 1 MK1805124694 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA Russian BFN [RIA report under the "In Brief" rubric: "Next Indexation in Summer"] [Text] Yet another indexation of minimum wages in the Russian Federation will take place next June-July, Russian Labor Minister Gennadiy Melikyan said. In his words, the minimum monthly wage in Russia will be increased approximately 1.4-fold, that is, to around 19,500 rubles.
